projectInfo.name: Mapping and validation of Maharajgunj Municipality
projectInfo.shortDescription:
As a part of the Booster grant by Open Mapping Hub- Asia Pacific to support the advancement of ongoing mapping and community building activities by the OSM Nepal community, we will be remotely mapping different parts of Nepal to map 1.5 million people on the map.

In this project, we will map Maharajganj Municipality which is a former village development committee and now is a Municipality in Kapilvastu District in the Lumbini Province of southern Nepal
projectInfo.description:
As a part of the Booster grant by Open Mapping Hub- Asia Pacific to support the advancement of ongoing mapping and community building activities by the OSM Nepal community, we will be remotely mapping different parts of Nepal to map 1.5 million people on the map.

In this project, we will map Maharajganj Municipality which is a former village development committee and now is a Municipality in Kapilvastu District in the Lumbini Province of southern Nepal
projectInfo.instructions:
Map buildings, roads, and waterways using free imagery provided by **Maxar Imagery**. 
To get started with Mapping watch this video <https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=r--thnVpk08>

If you are working with validation watch this video <https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=k-tVk_7IePM>

You will be using satellite imagery to map roads, buildings, waterways. For a guideline on remote mapping please refer to this wiki <https://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Nepal_remote_mapping_guide>

For a list of common tags used in Nepal please refer to this wiki <https://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Nepal/Common_tags>

For classification and tagging of roads please refer to this wiki <https://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Nepal/Roads>

To be efficient with mapping buildings we suggest you use JOSM with building plugin installed. Please note that most buildings in Nepal are rectangular in shape and what seems like circular huts could be a haystack.
